parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to be difficult to stop, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has to be depressed to the floorboard to stop the vehicle
the brake pedal extends to the floor when depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ABS sensor is melted or damaged
smoke emits from the front driver side brake
the calipers on the front driver side wheel stick in the applied position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic system can cause fires or loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Leaks in the hydraulic line
fire starts in the engine compartment area
hydraulic jacks malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power, power steering, and power brakes, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
sudden loss of engine power
power steering
and power brakes
burning smell or smoke from the ignition switch area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic system can cause the hydraulic jacks to malfunction, leading to difficulties in retracting or extending the jacks, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Hydraulic jacks fail to retract or extend
leak at fittings
hydraulic fluid leaks onto the exhaust manifold
causing a fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, leading to electrical fires, engine compartment fires, or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Water heater fails to ignite
resistor needs to be replaced
30-amp plug separates from the cord
electrical fires or sparks in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering System Vibration and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the steering wheel and loss of control can cause accidents, especially at high speeds, and may lead to a loss of confidence in the vehicle's handling.
symptoms: The steering wheel vibrates uncontrollably
the vehicle swerves or bounces while driving
the vehicle is difficult to control
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.
